  "prompt": "Does IIM Indore select 1 year dropouts for IPM?",
  "response": "Yes, **IIM Indore** does consider candidates who have **dropped out after completing one year** of their undergraduate program for admission to the **Integrated Programme in Management (IPM)**. However, there are specific eligibility criteria and conditions that such candidates must meet:\n\n### Eligibility Criteria for IPM at IIM Indore:\n1. **Educational Qualification**:  \n   - Candidates must have passed **Class XII/HSC or equivalent** with a minimum of **60%** (55% for SC/ST/PwD) in their qualifying examination.  \n   - Students who have dropped out after completing **one year** of their undergraduate program are eligible to apply, provided they meet the academic requirements.\n\n2. **Age Limit**:  \n   - The candidate\u2019s age should not exceed **20 years** (22 years for SC/ST/PwD) as of the date of admission.\n\n3. **Entrance Exam**:  \n   - Candidates must appear for the **IPMAT (Integrated Programme in Management Aptitude Test)**, conducted by IIM Indore, and secure a qualifying score.\n\n4. **Other Requirements**:  \n   - Candidates must provide valid proof of their academic records and dropout reasons.  \n   - IIM Indore may also consider the candidate\u2019s performance in **Personal Interview (PI)** and **Written Ability Test (WAT)** as part of the selection process.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Dropping out after one year does not disqualify you from applying, but **IIM Indore emphasizes academic consistency and performance**.  \n- You must ensure that your reason for dropping out does not negatively impact your candidacy during the selection process.\n\nIf you meet the eligibility criteria, you can apply for the IPM program at IIM Indore. For more details, refer to the **official IPMAT brochure** or the **IIM Indore website**.",
